  "name": "Mirai",
  "title": "Sparkling Idol",
  "secondName": "Sparkling Idol",
  "description": "Even as the world crumbles, nothing draws a crowd quite as big as Mirai's.  \n\nIt only makes sense that people line up in droves to see a Vessel in person. Never mind the ugly business of the Requiem. Mirai's voice is that of the Goddess, and it's said that all who hear it are blessed.  \n\nIndeed, reports of civil disturbance plummet in the wake of her concerts. Everyone seems just a little happier. Nothing actually changes for the people, of course. A happy song can't end a famine or turn back a flood. But it can make them forget for a time. \n\nIt's her duty to make them forget.",
